  if (!user.email) {
              throw new SelfHostedRegistrationError();
            }

we are still throwing this error why?

Yes—the first registering user is allowed regardless of email.

`firstUser` is poorly named: it means “a user already exists in the database.”

```ts
if (firstUser) {
  // This candidate is actually the second-or-later user.
  if (!user.email) {
    throw new SelfHostedRegistrationError();
  }
}
```

When the database is empty, `firstUser` is `null`, so the throw is skipped. Renaming it to `existingUser` or `registeredUser` would make this much clearer.

